chunk_content: Number of active DREAMS participants that have started a DREAMS service/intervention but have not yet completed it Indicator changes • Updated guiding narrative questions (MER v2.6.1 to v2.7): Reporting level: Community (Reported by USG team, not implementing partners) Reporting Semi-Annually frequency: How to use: This indicator reflects program data on how many AGYW are being served in DREAMS and how many active DREAMS participants have received the intended layered services/interventions to prevent HIV seroconversion. Specifically, this indicator will measure how many active DREAMS participants have completed the DREAMS primary package of services/interventions, the primary package plus any secondary services/interventions, and how many have not yet completed the primary package. Who is Captured Under AGYW_PREV: AGYW should only be counted under AGYW_PREV if they are an active DREAMS participant (see below for definition of active participant).
